First try to calculate VDR

The following screenshot shows our first try to derive the Vertical Distribution Ratio (VDR) by working with Fusion on one tile (LIDAR data) of the study area. The Canopy Height Model (CHM) for the whole study area is fully processed (visible underneath the tile). Something went wrong as there are many negative VDR values.

Arbeitsschritte um den VDR Index mit ArcGis zu berechnen:

  1. Las to raster
    • DGM: Binning: Zellenzuweisungstyp: Minimum; Abtastwert:1
    • DSM: Binning: Zellenzuweisungstyp: Maximum; Abtastwert:1
    • HOME: Binning: Zellenzuweisungstyp: Average; Abtastwert:1
  2. Raster Calculator: (DSM-HOME)/DSM
